reviewText: This documentary is very educational & very long. I suggest you drink some coffee to stay awake if you're going to watch it continuously all the way thru. The movie is excellent!
boring hated it couldn't watch it all.
My husband loves this dvd.  Arrived very quickly.
My boyfriend loved it !  He didn't realize it was a documentary with the real people on film and photos :  )
I loved it , a really good western!
Very educational.  Learned a lot about cowboys and  their lives.
It's good, but not quite what I expected.

This is a pretty good documentary, I grew up in the 50's and 60's and for a while I wanted to be a cowboy, at least until I learned they use pick up truck, motorcycles, atv's and helicopters these days. Rode horses and even got to participate in an old fashioned cattle drive as a youngster, was only a one day drive but I was in heaven. This documentary gives a a small glimpse of those days and of the rare men that protected the people and in some case did just the opposite. Price was great!
